11. Open Problems and Future Work

While this thesis provides a theoretical foundation, several open problems remain:

1. High‑fidelity PSI simulation for belief updates: Integrating CFD results into a lightweight surrogate model for real‑time inference, using recent Langley test data (Korzun et al., 2024) for calibration.
2. Formal convergence proofs for non‑linear EpiKF with coupled zones: Extend Lemma 1 to the multi‑zone case with physical interactions, under Maakoul’s control.
3. Scalable solution algorithms: Develop decentralized belief‑space MPC that respects zone autonomy while achieving global optimality.
4. Experimental validation: Conduct analog tests with regolith simulants and small‑scale plume experiments (e.g., Langley vacuum chamber hot‑fire tests) to calibrate models.
5. Integration with ISRU economics: Quantify the value of information in terms of reduced consumables or increased production.
6. Human‑in‑the‑loop epistemic control: Incorporate crew feedback as observations to reduce uncertainty about habitat conditions.

These directions are natural extensions of the current work and will be addressed in future research.

