Appendix B: Detailed EpiKF Equations

For zone i, let the augmented state be \xi = [x; \theta]. The dynamics:

\xi_{t+1} = g(\xi_t, u_t) + w_t, \quad w_t \sim \mathcal{N}(0, Q_t).

Observation:

y_t = h(\xi_t, u_t) + v_t, \quad v_t \sim \mathcal{N}(0, R_t).

The EpiKF prediction:

\hat{\xi}_{t|t-1} = g(\hat{\xi}_{t-1|t-1}, u_{t-1}), \quad P_{t|t-1} = G_t P_{t-1|t-1} G_t^\top + Q_t,

where G_t = \partial g/\partial \xi evaluated at \hat{\xi}_{t-1|t-1}.

Update:

K_t = P_{t|t-1} H_t^\top (H_t P_{t|t-1} H_t^\top + R_t)^{-1},

\hat{\xi}_{t|t} = \hat{\xi}_{t|t-1} + K_t (y_t - h(\hat{\xi}_{t|t-1}, u_t)),

P_{t|t} = (I - K_t H_t) P_{t|t-1},

with H_t = \partial h/\partial \xi evaluated at \hat{\xi}_{t|t-1}.

The epistemic uncertainty is measured by \text{tr}(P_{\theta\theta}).

